description:
&lt;p&gt;Following the transfer of paediatric inpatient care from the Royal Orthopaedic Hospital to Birmingham Children’s Hospital, the current service is expanding to support orthopaedic oncology surgery and increase inpatient spinal beds. There is an exciting opportunity for you to be part of a team that encompasses a reactive multi-disciplinary approach to both elective and emergency admissions to ensure that best practice is achieved.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 15 Annex will be the sister Ward of Ward 5 which currently specialises in Trauma and Orthopaedics and ENT. Ward 15 Annex is set to open January 2021 and will specialise in the immediate pre and post-operative treatment of children requiring endoprosthetic replacement (EPR) or amputation, following treatment for primary malignant bone tumours and also spinal surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are job opportunities on both wards or as a rotational post between both areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced Band 5 Registered Nurse, or newly qualified nurse, enabling you to join a team which offers unparalleled support for staff, including a dedicated Lead Nurse and 24/7 senior nursing team support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will also consider applications from Adult registered nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
